                1-888-567-8688. See <span style="font-weight:bold;">PRESCREEN & OPT-OUT</span> NOTICE for more information about prescreened offers.
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td colspan=3 style="padding-top:10px;">
              <div style="text-align:left; font-size:9.5px; line-height:10px;">
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS:</span> In the state of California, American Airlines Federal Credit Union credit cards are considered secured credit<br>
                cards. “Secured credit card” means any credit card issued under an agreement or other instrument that pledges, hypothecates or places<br>
                a lien on real property or money or other personal property to secure the cardholder’s obligations to the card issuer.
                <br><br>
                *Loans are subject to credit approval and Credit Union lending guidelines. In order to benefit from this offer, cardholder must keep <br>
                account in good standing. This offer is non-transferable and cannot be combined with any other offer. Annual fee: $0. Balance transfer <br>
                fee: $0. Cash advance fee: $2. Minimum finance charge: $.50 except where prohibited by law. International transaction fee: Rewards <br>
                Card is 0% and all other cards is 1% of transaction amount after its conversion to U.S.  dollars.
                <br><br>
                **Annual Percentage Rate (APR) – See table below for information about rates, fees and other costs concerning this card.<br>
                † APR National Average Source: Bankrate.com, accurate as of 11/14/2018.<br>
                American Airlines Credit Union and the Flight Symbol are marks of American Airlines, Inc.<br>
                Visa and Visa Checkout are registered trademarks of Visa International Service Association.
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td colspan=3>
              <img src="http://www.ericposas.com/images/connectionpoints.png" width=100 style="float:right">
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="text-align:left;">
            <td style="width: 100px; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #000; padding-left:5px;">
              Cards
            </td>
            <td style="width:240px; border:1px solid #000; padding-left:5px;">
              Visa® Platinum Low Rate
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #000; padding-left:5px;">
              Visa® Platinum Rewards
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="text-align:left;">
            <td colspan=3 style="font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #000; padding-left:5px;">
              Interest Rates and Interest Charges
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="font-size:11px">
            <td style="border:1px solid #000; text-align:left; line-height:14px; padding-left:5px; padding-top:4px; padding-bottom: 4px;">
              Annual Percentage<br> Rate (APR) for<br> Purchases
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #000; text-align:left; line-height:14px; padding-left:5px; padding-top:4px; padding-bottom: 4px;">
              <span style="font-size:17px">9.00% to 14.24%</span> when you open your<br> account, based on your creditworthiness. This<br> APR will vary with the market based on the<br> Prime Rate.
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #000; text-align:left; line-height:14px; padding-left:5px; padding-top:4px; padding-bottom: 4px;">
              <span style="font-size:17px">10.50% to 16.24%</span> when you open <br>your account, based on your creditworthiness. <br>This APR will vary with the market based on<br> the Prime Rate.
            </td>
          </tr>
